   <div id="erroneousinclusion-questions" type="gl-questions">
      <head>Questions and issues</head>
      <list type="simple">
         <item><name>Gabriel Bodard</name> (<date>2008-04-24</date>): we have now simplified the EpiDoc
         recommendation on this issue to that <tag>sic</tag> without a parent::<tag>choice</tag> represents
         a superfluous character, but <tag>sic</tag> within <tag>choice</tag> (and parallel to <tag>corr</tag>)
         represents an erroneously executed character (see <xref>erroneoussubstitution.xml</xref>).</item>
         <item><name>Gabriel Bodard</name> (<date value="2005-05-17">2006-03-21</date>): I would
            suggest we deprecate number 2 the empty <tag>corr</tag> element which now does not add
            any flexibility in terms of mixed content in text vs attribute nodes. <note>DONE: GB</note></item>
         <item><name>Gabriel Bodard</name> (<date value="2005-05-17">2006-07-16</date>): I would
            also suggest we quit abusing the <att>n</att> attribute and customise the schema to
            allow <att>type</att> or <att>reason</att> (vel sim.)</item>
      </list>
   </div>
